reviewText:
+ colorful, pretty detailed graphics;
+ satisfying platforming and collectibles hunting;
+ music - just what you would expect;
+ tons of unlockables;
+ low requirements;
+ makes the prequels look cool in its setting;
+ simplistic, but effective storytelling;
+ beautiful, open locations;

- don't expect a challenge, apart from a few puzzles and some frustrating segments, it's easy;
- Jar Jar.

Fun for all ages. Recommended.
